HEADWORD: Trachelidan
<hw>Tra*chel"i*dan</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/
neck.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one of a tribe of beetles
(<fam>Trachelides</fam>) which have the head supported on a pedicel. The
oil beetles and the Cantharides are examples.</def>⟦br⟧
